#. <section class="sutta" id="sn54.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn54.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 54"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 54"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn54.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Ekadhammavagga"
msgstr "1. One Thing"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 9. Vesālīsutta → asubhasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn54.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Vesālīsutta"
msgstr "9. At Vesālī"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.9:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn54.9:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "sn54.9:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ anekapariyāyena asubhakathaṃ "
"katheti, asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, asubhabhāvanāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Buddha spoke in many ways to the mendicants about the "
"meditation on ugliness. He praised the meditation on ugliness and its "
"development."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.9:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn54.9:2.2"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, bhikkhave, aḍḍhamāsaṃ paṭisallīyituṃ."
msgstr "“Mendicants, I wish to go on retreat for a fortnight."

msgctxt "sn54.9:2.3"
msgid "Nāmhi kenaci upasaṅkamitabbo, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakenā”ti."
msgstr "No-one should approach me, except for the one who brings my alms-food.”"

msgctxt "sn54.9:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā nāssudha koci "
"bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamati, aññatra ekena piṇḍapātanīhārakena."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied those mendicants. And no-one approached him, except for "
"the one who brought the alms-food."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.9:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū:"
msgstr "Then those mendicants thought:"

msgctxt "sn54.9:3.2"
msgid ""
"“bhagavā anekapariyāyena asubhakathaṃ katheti, asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
"asubhabhāvanāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsatī”ti anekākāravokāraṃ "
"asubhabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha spoke in many ways about the meditation on ugliness. He praised "
"the meditation on ugliness and its development.” They committed themselves "
"to developing the many different aspects of the meditation on ugliness."

#. VAR: aṭṭīyamānā → aṭṭiyamānā (si, s1-3, km, mr) | aṭṭiyāmānā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn54.9:3.3"
msgid ""
"Te iminā kāyena aṭṭīyamānā harāyamānā jigucchamānā satthahārakaṃ pariyesanti."
msgstr ""
"Becoming horrified, repelled, and disgusted with this body, they looked for "
"someone to slit their wrists."

msgctxt "sn54.9:3.4"
msgid ""
"Dasapi bhikkhū ekāhena satthaṃ āharanti, vīsampi … pe … tiṃsampi bhikkhū "
"ekāhena satthaṃ āharanti."
msgstr "Each day ten, twenty, or thirty mendicants slit their wrists."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.321"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.9:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā tassa aḍḍhamāsassa accayena paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito āyasmantaṃ "
"ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then after a fortnight had passed, the Buddha came out of retreat and "
"addressed Ānanda:"

msgctxt "sn54.9:4.2"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, ānanda, tanubhūto viya bhikkhusaṅgho”ti?"
msgstr "“Ānanda, why does the mendicant Saṅgha seem so diminished?”"

msgctxt "sn54.9:4.3"
msgid ""
"“Tathā hi pana, bhante, ‘bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ anekapariyāyena asubhakathaṃ "
"katheti, asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, asubhabhāvanāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsatī’ti "
"anekākāravokāraṃ asubhabhāvanānuyogamanuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr "Ānanda told the Buddha all that had happened, and said:"

msgctxt "sn54.9:4.4"
msgid ""
"Te iminā kāyena aṭṭīyamānā harāyamānā jigucchamānā satthahārakaṃ pariyesanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn54.9:4.5"
msgid ""
"Dasapi bhikkhū ekāhena satthaṃ āharanti, vīsampi bhikkhū … tiṃsampi bhikkhū "
"ekāhena satthaṃ āharanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn54.9:4.6"
msgid ""
"Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā aññaṃ pariyāyaṃ ācikkhatu yathāyaṃ bhikkhusaṅgho "
"aññāya saṇṭhaheyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, please explain another way for the mendicant Saṅgha to get "
"enlightened.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.9:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Tenahānanda, yāvatikā bhikkhū vesāliṃ upanissāya viharanti te sabbe "
"upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannipātehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, Ānanda, gather all the mendicants staying in the vicinity of "
"Vesālī together in the assembly hall.”"

msgctxt "sn54.9:5.2"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā yāvatikā bhikkhū "
"vesāliṃ upanissāya viharanti te sabbe upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannipātetvā yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda. He did what the Buddha asked, went up to him, "
"and said:"

#. VAR: sannipatito → sannipātito (si)
msgctxt "sn54.9:5.3"
msgid "“sannipatito, bhante, bhikkhusaṃgho."
msgstr "“Sir, the mendicant Saṅgha has assembled."

msgctxt "sn54.9:5.4"
msgid "Yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ maññatī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, sir, come at your convenience.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.9:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā yena upaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte "
"āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha went to the assembly hall, sat down on the seat spread out,"

msgctxt "sn54.9:6.2"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn54.9:6.3"
msgid ""
"“ayampi kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi bhāvito bahulīkato santo ceva "
"paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale "
"dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is "
"developed and cultivated it’s peaceful and sublime, a deliciously pleasant "
"meditation. And it disperses and settles unskillful qualities on the spot "
"whenever they arise."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.322"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.9:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gimhānaṃ pacchime māse ūhataṃ rajojallaṃ, tamenaṃ "
"mahāakālamegho ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti;"
msgstr ""
"In the last month of summer, when the dust and dirt is stirred up, a large "
"sudden storm disperses and settles it on the spot."

msgctxt "sn54.9:7.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi bhāvito bahulīkato santo ceva "
"paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale "
"dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is "
"developed and cultivated it’s peaceful and sublime, a deliciously pleasant "
"meditation. And it disperses and settles unskillful qualities on the spot "
"whenever they arise."

msgctxt "sn54.9:7.3"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ bhāvito ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi kathaṃ bahulīkato santo "
"ceva paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale "
"dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti?"
msgstr "And how is it so developed and cultivated?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn54.9:8.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā "
"nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ "
"upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to "
"an empty hut—sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and focuses "
"their mindfulness right there."

msgctxt "sn54.9:8.2"
msgid "So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe …"
msgstr "Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out. …"

msgctxt "sn54.9:8.3"
msgid ""
"‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī "
"passasissāmī’ti sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They "
"practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’"

msgctxt "sn54.9:8.4"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ bhāvito kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhi evaṃ bahulīkato santo ceva "
"paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale "
"dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasametī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how this immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and "
"cultivated so that it’s peaceful and sublime, a deliciously pleasant "
"meditation. And it disperses and settles unskillful qualities on the spot "
"whenever they arise.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn54.9:8.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
